Junior Motocross riders will make their way to the host city of Vantaa, Finland, to compete against the best junior riders in the 2022 FIM Junior Motocross World Championship and the FIM Junior Motocross World Cup. The event will be held at the legendary tracks of Ruskeasanta and Lavanko from August 26 to 28. The opening ceremony will take place in the centre of Vantaa in Tikkurila on Friday August 26.  The appointed South African team manager, Neville Townsend, team captain, Trey Cox, and the MSA Motocross Commission are pleased to announce the following team who will proudly represent South Africa. Source: Motorsport SA